This paper investigates the effect of a performance-based research funding system on the citation impact of papers authored by Turkish researchers. The study focuses on the impact of publication support system on scholarly papers, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and cryptography (cs.CR).
